    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="561"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/183.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Dominican Minister</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dominican Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 22, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary</hi>: I have the honor to send to you herewith
                    in Spanish, marked No. 1, the minutes of the six conferences that we have had
                        <pb facs="0503" n="387" xml:id="pg_387"/> at the Department of State
                    relating to the settlement of the boundary dispute pending between the Dominican
                    Republic and the Republic of Haiti, signed by the Haitian Plenipotentiary and by
                        me.<note n="1" xml:id="d561fn1">Not printed. The minutes are not dated;
                        those of the sixth meeting show a formal exchange of the views expressed
                        informally at the fifth meeting, as summarized in the memorandum of July
                        10.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Since the 13th of last July there has been no exchange of views between the two
                    plenipotentiaries other than those of August 8 last; copies<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d561fn2">Not printed; they continue the same matters discussed at
                        the fifth and sixth meetings.</note> of these are enclosed, marked Nos. 2
                    and 3.</p>
                <p>I avail [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fran’co J. Peynado.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
